						               													<description>In Stalin Assassin, each player is randomly assigned a role.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;4 possible roles at the start: Stalin, Commis, Capitalists and The Bolshevik. The Capitalists always have a majority, the Commis know who they are the Capitalists and Commis do not know who is Stalin or The Bolshevik.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Stalin and The Bolshevik are always in incognito and also do not know who they are.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;5 to 11 players:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;5 players - 2 Capitalists, 1 Commi, 1 Stalin and 1 Bolshevik&amp;#10;&amp;#10;6 and 7 players - 3 or 4 Capitalists, 1 Commi, 1 Stalin and 1 Bolshevik&amp;#10;&amp;#10;8 to 11 players - 3 Commi, 1 Stalin, 1 Bolshevik and all other Capitalists&amp;#10;&amp;#10;HAMMER OF POWER passes from a player to the other and all players have to put their thumbs up or down to accept the HAMMER of POWER (POWER TOOL OR PT) given to the player selected. If the player gets most okays he picks 2 cards and places his chosen one on the board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There is 1 board where actions are taken. 11 action in total. 1&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each time the HAMMER OF POWER is passed to a player. That player takes 2 TOOL Cards and places 1 on the BOARD (COMMI POWER TOOL or FREEDOM CARD). Then he places the one not chosen back in the pile of cards *at the bottom).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If at action 3 and 4 there is a COMMI POWER TOOL - TIME FOR WILD GUESS - where all will guess who is a Commi The &amp;quot;appointed&amp;quot; Commi gets an UNDERCOVER COMMI card and is suspected to be a Commi.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The board is called Mother Russia.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
